# Repository Migration System — Final Plan (10/10) v3

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Target structure:** `Topic/Difficulty/Problem/solution.ext`
> ```
> Array/Easy/0001-two-sum/solution.cpp
> String/Medium/0003-longest-substring/solution.py
> ```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Two legacy layouts supported:**
> ```
> Layout A — "legacy-flat-folder"        Layout B — "legacy-flat-root" (LeetHub v2)
> problems/                              0001-two-sum/
>     0001-two-sum/                          solution.cpp
>         solution.cpp                   0002-add-two-numbers/
>     0002-add-two-numbers/                  solution.cpp
>         solution.cpp                   README.md
>                                        stats.json
> ```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Metadata resolution priority:**
> ```
> 1. Metadata Cache     ← chrome.storage, 7-day TTL (fastest)
> 2. LeetCode GraphQL   ← authoritative source
> 3. Repository metadata ← leetsync.json / manifest.json if present
> 4. Uncategorized/      ← last resort
> ```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Execution strategy: Git Data API (atomic batch commits)**
> ```
> OLD (per-file, thousands of API calls):
>   GET blob → PUT file → DELETE file → repeat × 1000
>
> NEW (batch, ~5 API calls per batch of 500):
>   Create blobs → Build tree → Create commit → Update ref
>   One atomic commit. No partial states. 10x fewer API calls.
> ```

