## Phase 0 — Repository Validation & Pre-flight Checks

**Goal:** Validate everything before migration starts. Block on hard failures, warn on soft issues.

### [NEW] `src/background/migration/validator.ts`

**Pre-flight checks:**

| # | Check | Fail Behavior |
|---|-------|--------------|
| 1 | GitHub Connected | **BLOCK** |
| 2 | Token Valid (`getUser`) | **BLOCK** |
| 3 | Repo Exists (`getRepo`) | **BLOCK** |
| 4 | Branch Exists (`default_branch`) | **BLOCK** |
| 5 | Write Permission (`repo.permissions.push`) | **BLOCK** |
| 6 | API Budget (`remaining >= estimated * 1.2`) | **WARN** + show wait time |
| 7 | LeetCode Reachable (test GraphQL) | **WARN** (will use cache/fallback) |
| 8 | Repo Type (no `package.json`, `Cargo.toml`, etc.) | **WARN** |
| 9 | Storage Space (`chrome.storage.local` quota) | **WARN** |
| 10 | **Migration Lock** — no other migration in progress | **BLOCK** |

**Migration lock (prevents concurrent execution):**
```ts
interface MigrationLock {
  active: boolean;
  lockedAt: string;       // ISO timestamp
  lockedBy: string;       // random session ID
  expiresAt: string;      // auto-expire after 30 minutes of inactivity
}

async function acquireLock(): Promise<boolean>
async function releaseLock(): Promise<void>
async function isLocked(): Promise<boolean>
```

Lock is stored in `chrome.storage.local`. If two popup windows are open, only one can acquire the lock. Lock auto-expires after 30 minutes to handle crashes.

Every executor heartbeat (after each move) refreshes the lock's `expiresAt`.

